HEADWORD: Extrados
<hw>Ex*tra"dos</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; pref.
<ets>extra-</ets> outside + <ets>dos</ets> (L. <ets>dorsum</ets>) the
back.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The exterior curve of an arch;
esp., the upper curved face of the whole body of voussoirs. See
<er>Intrados</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

